In Ghana, divorce is not a common occurrence and is not encouraged by the society. The stigma attached to divorce is so strong that it is not uncommon for a woman to be shunned by her family and friends if she gets a divorce. This is because divorce is seen as a sign of failure and a woman who gets a divorce is seen as a failure.
